&lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/philosophy/domains/western/domains/epistemology/texts/knowledge-and-documentation-survey/>
  rdf:type schema:Article ;
  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/philosophy/domains/western/domains/epistemology/texts/knowledge-and-documentation-survey/> ;
  schema:name "Knowledge and Documentation: A Survey of Their Relationship" ;
  schema:description "Survey of competing accounts of how knowledge relates to its recording — from Plato's separation of knowledge from writing through Briet's documentation theory, Polanyi's tacit dimension, Dewey's inquiry, archival diplomatics, and Haraway's situated knowledges. Maps the terrain between knowledge as a mental state and documentation as its constitutive practice." ;
